    <h3>Getting Started</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Associate your license under Nooklyn.com with our training manager.</li>
      <li>Sign our agreements (Confidentiality, Independent Contractor, W9).</li>
      <li>Sign up on nooklyn.com and upload a profile photo. </li>
      <li>Learn how to use the matrix, Groupme, Dropbox, receive free company email and business cards.</li>
      <li>Update your voicemail, LinkedIn, and other social media accounts with your new awesome position.</li>
      <li>Get to know the listings, view them and take photos, understanding our availability’s is everything.</li>
      <li>Get familiar with our simple paperwork process.</li>
      <li>Market listings. Post, post, post, until your fingers bleed.</li>
      <li>Create accounts with, nakedapartments.com, craigslist.org, padlister.com and postlets.com.</li>
      <li>Hit up your local business with our template flyers and your business cards.</li>
      <li>Shadow a senior agent on 3-5 appointments. Listen, learn and ask questions after the showing.</li>
      <li>You MUST have a senior agent or training manager present to your first 3 appointments and present to your first 3-5 deposits.</li>
    </ol>
    <h3>Trial Period</h3>
    <p>Everyone starts with a 60-day trial period you must close 5 deals within the probationary trial period. After closing 5 deals independently you are eligible for a performance review and commission increase.</p>
    <p>You are required to close a minimum of 24 residential leases annually.</p>
    <p>You must attend office meetings. If you absolutely cannot attend you must give notice.</p>
    <p>After your first 30 days you must meet with your  training manager to go over anything you may need help with.</p>
    <h3>Customer Service</h3>
    <p class="lead">We love our clients - Let’s keep them!</p>
    <p>Awesome customer service separates us from the competition.</p>
    <p>Zero tolerance for poor attitudes, mistreating, and misrepresenting our customers. Moving absolutely sucks! It’s your job to make it suck a lot less. Without our clients we aren’t in business.</p>
    <p>Close more deals and leave your clients happy by being non-pushy, honest, transparent and always offering a clear and timely resolutions when issues arise. </p>
    <p>Don’t promise ANYTHING you can’t 100% positively deliver. In every scenario “I will gladly find out for you” is always the correct response. If you find yourself in a difficult position, do not ignore it, instill confidence that Nooklyn staff will work towards a solution. Give your clients a time frame for resolution and stick to it. </p>
    <p>Be personable, make friends, have fun and most importantly, always follow through. Brokers have a bad rep, so show your clients you’re a real human. Entertain them, make interesting or humorous conversation. Clients respond best when you help them as friend, advise them as if you were moving in together, demonstrate your integrity and strategic help by listening to their needs and going the extra mile.</p>
    <p>Customer service is a group effort and your coworkers can be hurting your pockets. If you are aware of co-workers not meeting customer service standards, bring them to our attention or first have a private conversation with them.</p>
    <p>Separate yourself from the hundreds of bad brokers. Keep in touch with your clients, call them back even after they move in. Building these personal relationships with your clients gets you referrals to both clients and landlords. </p>
    <ol>
      <li>Kindly greet anyone visiting our offices offer them water, and find them a seat. </li>
      <li>Call each client back timely.</li>
      <li>Give each client a business card.</li>
      <li>Never pull a no-show. If this happens accidently, apologize profusely and send a coworker if you can’t show. </li>
      <li>Be transparent with apt details, utilities, lease terms, our fee’s, move in dates, etc.</li>
      <li>Follow up with your clients.</li>
      <li>Keep a detailed list of all your customers and reach back out to them often.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>Common resolution to unhappy customers (Approval needed):</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Possibility of partial or lowered fee and or applications fees via approval from Senior/Listing/Nooklyn management. </li>
      <li>Lowering our broker fees. </li>
      <li>Hiring professional services, such as, movers, maids, painters, etc.</li>
    </ul>
