    <h3>Application Process</h3>
    <p>Our deposits are almost always refundable in order to uphold our commitment to customer service. Our minimum good faith deposit is $500 (24hr time limit) but try to get one full month. Some landlords require a full month deposit payable to them or use an online payment system so you must check with the listing agent prior to taking a deposit.</p>
    <p>Paperwork and follow though is everything!</p>
    <p>The goal is to obtain all required paperwork and get a lease executed within 24 hours – 48 hours. The longer you wait risks your clients changing their mind.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>A deposit does not guarantee a property off the market, it starts the paperwork process in good faith. </li>
      <li>Call the listing agent to verify, listings availability, apt details, application process, and pets. </li>
      <li>Check on,  price, apt #, move in date; total move in cost, utilities, our fees and any amenities.</li>
      <li>If the listing agent is unavailable, take the deposit and get back to your clients after verification.</li>
      <li>Label a Manila folder for this application to collect paperwork, include apt address, unit # in the tab</li>
      <li> All NOOKLYN paperwork is located on our DROPBOX or printed out for you in each office.</li>
      <li>Complete a deposit agreement / NY state disclosure form.</li>
      <li>Get a photocopy of each applicant’s driver’s license or passport.</li>
      <li>Have each applicant complete a rental application; check to make sure it’s completed properly.</li>
      <li>Cash deposits label an envelope, with address, apt #, deposit amount, date, and your name.</li>
      <li> Application fees accepted in cash should be labeled separate from then the deposit on your envelope.</li>
      <li>Cash must be left with office admin or designated deposit boxes. You may never hold on to funds.</li>
      <li>Chase quick pay has no transaction fees.  </li>
      <li>Paypal and credit cards have a 2.9% convenience fee.</li>
      <li>When processing online payments, make sure your client includes, your name, apt #, address.</li>
      <li>Collect application fees for each applicant and each co-signer at time of deposit.</li>
      <li>Ask clients to print out proof of income at the office.</li>
      <li>Clients can also email/ fax paperwork, advise them to include apt # and address applying for.</li>
      <li>Update listing status on the matrix and group me. </li>
      <li>It is your responsibility to follow up with your clients and collect paperwork within 24-48 hours.</li>
      <li>Scan and email all paperwork received to the listing agent, in addition, print it out and add to your file.</li>
      <li> Remember, deposits are NOT closed deals.</li>
      <li>After your receive an approval coordinate a lease singing with the listing agent. </li>
      <li>Rejected deposits will be returned only by company check at the Bushwick office.</li>
      <li>Applications can only be shared with building owner, representatives, and our administration. </li>
      <li>Assure clients / co signers  financial information is confidential and we use online fax for added security. </li>
    </ul>
