    <h3>Broker Fees</h3>
    <p>Broker fees are payable to: NOOKLYN.COM LLC.</p>
    <p>All other payments in this transaction including first, last, and security, are payable to the landlord directly. Our fees can be negotiable this gives you the flexibility to close more deals. Check with the listing agent for approval prior to negotiating fees with your clients.</p>
    <h3>Owner Pays</h3>
    <p>OP stands for (owner pays)</p>
    <p>Collect only the amount of commission the owner pays, payable to NOOKLYN.COM LLC.</p>
    <p>Most common OP ‘s are, 50%, 70%, 100% of one months rent. First, last, and security are payable to the landlord minus the percentage we collected for our fee.</p>
    <h3>Landlord Payments</h3>
    <p>Before you instruct your clients to pay any funds to a landlord, confirm with the listing agent whom to make checks payable to.</p>
    <p>Listing agents: when paying a landlord please give office administration 24 hours to process a check unless it’s an emergency.</p>
    <h3>Application Fees</h3>
    <p>Each application and  each co-signer must pay a $75 NON- REFUNDABLE application fee to cover processing their application.</p>
    <p>In some cases, if our clients are dissatisfied or we are at fault, we will lower the application fee to $25.00 per person or if the credit report was not processed we will refund application fees entirely. You must get approval for this first.</p>
    <p>Please take all application fees at the time of the deposit.</p>
    <p>If your client cannot pay application fees at time of deposit or obtains additional applicants and/or co-signer’s you are responsible to collect these application fees.</p>
    <p>Unpaid application fees will be taken from your commission check at $50 per applicant.</p>
    <p>Administration approved application fee discounts must be notated on the deposit agreement.</p>
    <p>Administration approved application fees waived must be notated on the deposit agreement.</p>
