    <h3>Splits / co broking</h3>
    <h4>With other Agencies:</h4>
    <p>You must sign a co-broke commission agreement with any cooperating real estate agent / agency. You are splitting a deal. If total commission is $2000 and your current rate is 40% and cooperating agent is getting 50% of the commission's. YOU will invoice at 20% of the total commission and your cooperating agent will invoice at 25% of the total commission. </p>
    <h4>Between Two Nooklyn Agents:</h4>
    <p>If you split a deal with another Nooklyn agent, you must agree upon how you are splitting the commision before the deposit is taken. If there is not an agreement before hand, it will be split 50/50 to avoid all conflict. Keep it friendly! We all work together often and you don’t want piss off your fellow agents!</p>
